      • registerClient

        public void registerClient(FilterClient f)
        Add a listener to the PwnFilter ListenerManager. This allows PwnFilter to notify the listener when it should try to activate or shutdown. PwnFilter will call the activate / shutdown methods when reloading rules configs.

        The FilterListener must register *before* attempting to use any other PwnFilter resources.

        Parameters:
        f - FilterListener instance

      • unregisterClient

        public boolean unregisterClient(FilterClient f)
        Remove a listener from the PwnFilter ListenerManager. The listener will no longer be activated / deactivated when PwnFilter reloads configs, rules, etc. IMPORTANT: Before de-registering, the FilterListener must remove all references to RuleSets.
        Parameters:
        f - FilterListener to remove.
        Returns:
        true if the listener was previously registered and successfully removed. False if it was not registered.
